<A NAME=18Line Item Veto>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>Line Item Veto</H3><BR>
IN WASHINGTON, THE SUPREME COURT IS CONSIDERING THE CONSTITUTIONALITY OF THE PRESIDENTIAL POWER OF LINE ITEM VETO.
<P>
ALMOST EVERY PRESIDENT THIS CENTURY HAS SOUGHT THE POWER TO VETO "PART" OF A BILL WITHOUT KILLING IT ENTIRELY.
<P>
CRITICS CHARGE THE LINE ITEM GIVES THE PRESIDENT THE POWER TO MAKE LAW, WHICH CONSTITUTIONALLY, IS CONGRESS' JOB.
<P>
SUPPORTERS TOLD THE COURT YESTERDAY THE LINE ITEM ALLOWS A PRESIDENT TO REMOVE WASTEFULL SPENDING IN BILLS AND DOES NOT VIOLATE THE CONSTITUTION'S SEPARATION OF POWER BETWEEN THE PRESIDENT AND CONGRESS.
<P>
THE LINE ITEM VETO WAS ENACTED IN 19-96.
<P>

